# Student Registration Form

## HTML Tags Used

<html> – Defines the root of the HTML document.
<head> – Contains information about the webpage, such as the title.
<title>– Sets the title displayed on the browser tab.
<body> – Contains all the visible content of the webpage
<h1> – Displays the main heading of the page.
<form> – Creates a form to collect user information.
<label> – Provides a label or description for an input field.
<input>– Creates different types of input fields (text, email, password, radio, etc.).
<br>– Inserts a line break between elements.
<select>– Creates a drop-down list.
<option> – Defines the items inside a drop-down list.
<textarea>– Creates a multi-line text input area.
<button> – Creates a clickable button to submit the form.
